<subSubSection id="C32123E5FFF8485FFF73FBAFFEB45802" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B84706EFFF8485FFF73FBAFFEB45802" blockId="9.[95,719,1082,1651]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFF73FBAFFF095A22" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[133,231,1082,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFF73FBAFFF095A22" box="[133,231,1082,1107]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epectasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFDDDFBAFFD205A22" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1839" box="[555,718,1082,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pogonocherini">Pogonocherini</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFF73FBCFFE7E5A02" authority="Bates, 1866" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[133,400,1114,1139]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="attenuata">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFF73FBCFFEE75A02" box="[133,265,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">E. attenuata</emphasis>
Bates, 1866
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFE40FBCFFF745AE2" authority="Newman, 1840" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1840" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Saperda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juncea">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFE40FBCFFDB25A02" box="[438,604,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Saperda juncea</emphasis>
Newman, 1840
</taxonomicName>
), from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C30FEFFF8485FFF1DFBEFFEC95AE2" box="[235,295,1146,1171]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Amazonas). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA0D9FFFF8485FFE37FBEFFD6B5AE2" author="Lacordaire, J. T." box="[449,645,1146,1171]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="411 - 930" refId="ref10361" refString="Lacordaire, J. T. 1872. Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Genera des Coleopteres, ou expose methodique et critique de tous les genres proposes jusqu'ici dans cet ordre d'insectes. Paris, Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, v. 9, pt. 2, p. 411 - 930." type="book chapter" year="1872">Lacordaire (1872)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFF51FB0FFEE75AC2" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[167,265,1178,1203]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFF51FB0FFEE75AC2" box="[167,265,1178,1203]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epectasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to Estolini, currently a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFFA9FB2FFF175AA2" authorityName="J. Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[95,249,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Desmiphorini">Desmiphorini</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA0D9FFFF8485FFEF7FB2FFE675AA2" author="Bates, H. W." box="[257,393,1210,1235]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="17 - 152" refId="ref9944" refString="Bates, H. W. 1880. Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera. London. v. 5, p. 17 - 152." type="journal article" year="1880">Bates (1880)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFE01FB2FFD215AA2" authority="in Ataxiini" authorityName="in Ataxiini" box="[503,719,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFE01FB2FFDB75AA2" box="[503,601,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epectasis</emphasis>
in Ataxiini
</taxonomicName>
(currently, equal to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFEC3FB4FFE455A82" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[309,427,1242,1267]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pteropliini">Pteropliini</taxonomicName>
):“I propose to include it in the “groupe” Ptéropliides of the ‘Genera,’ and the genera 
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFFA9FA8FFE8D5B42" box="[95,355,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFFA9FA8FFF2D5B42" authority="Bates, 1866" box="[95,195,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epectasis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFF39FA8FFEB15B42" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[207,351,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Amphicnaeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amphicnaeia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFE57FA8FFDEF5B42" box="[417,513,1306,1331]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFE57FA8FFE135B42" authority="Bates, 1866" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1866" box="[417,509,1306,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aletretia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aletretia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
which have been hitherto placed in widely different groups.” 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA0D9FFFF8485FFD97FAAFFF4B5B02" author="Aurivillius, C." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="323 - 704" refId="ref9916" refString="Aurivillius, C. 1923. Coleopterorum Catalogus, pars 74, Cerambycidae: Lamiinae. Berlin, W. Junk. p. 323 - 704." type="book chapter" year="1923">Aurivillius (1923)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFED1FACFFE675B02" authority="in Emphytoeciini" authorityName="in Emphytoeciini" box="[295,393,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFED1FACFFE675B02" box="[295,393,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epectasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFE36FACFFD8C5B02" authority="in Emphytoeciini" authorityName="in Emphytoeciini" box="[448,610,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Emphytoeciini</taxonomicName>
, currently under synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFE9AFAEFFE0F5BE2" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[364,481,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pteropliini">Pteropliini</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFE19FAEFFDBF5BE2" authority="Bates, 1866" box="[495,593,1402,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFE19FAEFFDBF5BE2" box="[495,593,1402,1427]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epectasis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains a problematic genus, with evident different species often being identified as a single species. This is notably true regarding 
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFF27FA4FFED85B82" box="[209,310,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFF27FA4FFEDC5B82" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1840" box="[209,306,1498,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Saperda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juncea">E.juncea</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
It is possible to note in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA0D9FFFF8485FFDCFFA4FFD205B82" author="Bezark, L. G." box="[569,718,1498,1523]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref9971" refString="Bezark, L. G. 2018. A photographic Catalog of the Cerambycidae of the New World. Available at: https: // apps 2. cdfa. ca. gov / publicApps / plant / bycidDB / wsearch. asp? w = n. Access in: 10 / 2018." type="url" year="2018">Bezark (2018)</bibRefCitation>
that some species with remarkable differences are being identified as 
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFF1AF98FFEBF5842" box="[236,337,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFF1AF98FFEA35842" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1840" box="[236,333,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Saperda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juncea">E. juncea</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, it is not the scope of this work to deal with these problems in 
<emphasis id="B94FAC7CFFF8485FFDF3F9AFFD835822" box="[517,621,1594,1619]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C3B0BEDFFF8485FFDF3F9AFFD875822" authority="Bates, 1866" box="[517,617,1594,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Epectasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epectasis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a genus needing a full revision.
</paragraph>
